Armed police have sealed off Hackney Central train station in East London after a boy was reporedly "stabbed" in broad daylight. A London Air Ambulance has been seen flying above the station and there are also ambulances and police at the scene. National Rail said police have evacuated and closed Hackney Central station while they deal with an "incident"  One Twitter user wrote: "OMG someone just got stabbed at Hackney Central station." In a separate post just minutes later, the they wrote: "I saw them wheeling away a boy with an oxygen mask on" with another post that read: "So weird seeing police with guns." A British Transport Police spokesperson said: "Following reports of an incident at 1.29pm today (1 March), armed officers are currently on scene at Hackney Central railway station. "One man has been taken to a local hospital and the station is closed while officers make enquiries into the incident." Transport for London Access (@TfLAccess has tweeted to say the station has been closed while "police carry out an investigation". We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: /news Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on facebook.com/DailyExpress and @daily_express 